
####TMUX ####
place .tmux.conf under ~/ (home folder) 
for applying globally for other users place under /etc/

tmux contains 

sessions
windows
panes

note when I say prefix h ---> ctrl+a release and press h
if command is prefix+h -----> then hold all keys together ctrl+a+h

just wanted to highlate difference between space and + in below commands


1.prefix is **ctrl+a** 
2.to create a session
	just we can use **tmux**
	but better to name it and start **tmux new -s session_name**
        or **tmux new-session session_name**
 
3.**prefix r** for refreshing tmux.conf
4.to create pane vertically **prefix v**
5.to create pane horizontally **prefix h**
6.move across panes by **alt+arrows** or **prefix arrows**
7.even we can use mouse to move between panes, for selecting text lines, blocks, copy paste
8. for copy select text with mouse(highlated in yellow),select text dont leave mouse, press enter. now text is selected.
9. to paste inside tmux use **ctrl+shift+v**
10. to paste in system console **ctrl+v**
11. copy from console normally **ctrl+c** for pasting inside tmux use **ctrl+shift+v**
12. active session is highlated
13. to change name of session **prefix $**
    to change name of window **prfix ,**
14. to zoom into one pane **prefix z**
15. to increase size of pane **prefix+z**
16. to increase size of font **prefix+shift++(plus)**
17. to decrease size of font **prefix+shift+-(minus)**
18. to create new window **prefix+c**
19. in case of multiple sessions - 
      to list sessions **tmux ls**
      to attach a session **tmux a -t session_name**
      to kill  a session **tmux kill-ses -t session_name**
      to kill all sessions **tmux kill-ses -a**
      to kill all but not mine  **tmux kill-session -a -t mysession**
.

